14. None of this absolves Hillary of any wrongdoing. But it is a terrible indictment of Trump's disrespect for what makes America great.
13. Because a president who talks flippantly about his power (putting rival in jail, ordering war crimes) IS flippant about using power.
12. "That's just how Trump talks" doesn't cut it. How presidents talk, especially about using his power, matters a lot.
11. Trump's flippant way of threatening to put his opponent in prison, rather than pursue justice even-handedly, is ominous.
10. Coupled with promises to muzzle unfriendly journalists and order military to commit war crimes, Trump's threat IS ominous.
9. US Presidential candidates need to be careful to not even create the impression they might engage in this kind of abuse.
8. China today is a good example. Many officials being sent to jail were corrupt, but their real crime was not being on Xi Jinping's team.
7. There are countries where political victors put rivals in jail. Even if those rivals ARE corrupt, real purpose is vengeance, deterrence.
6. The president ought to be careful and judicious in addressing potential wrong-doing, especially by political rivals.
5. The president is the nation's chief law enforcement officer, not just a political combatant.
